  Rodriguez drive the initiatives and programs to cultivate a climate of diversity and equity in which individual students  faculty  and staff feel welcomed  valued for their contributions  and feel their identities can be openly expressed  Alex Stagnaro Green  Dean of the University of Illinois College of Medicine at Rockford  conducting innovative research  and dedicated to improving the health and wellness of our society  Dr  Dr  Rodriguez will work with the Offices of Student and Academic Affairs in addressing issues of climate for diverse student populations Dr  Rodriguez will continue his practice as a cosmetic and reconstructive plastic surgeon with OSF Cosmetic and Reconstructive Plastic Surgery in Rockford  Illinois  A graduate of Michigan State University College of Human Medicine  he completed his general surgical residency at SUMMA Health System in Akron  Ohio  followed by a plastic surgery fellowship at the University of Illinois at Chicago  Certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery  Dr  Rodriguez has received numerous awards including the Faculty   Staff Aureus Award  the Excellence in Teaching Award  the Chicago Society of Plastic Surgeons Research Award  and numerous others Education MD Admissions Rockford Interviews MD Curriculum Campus Specific Programs Clinician Executive Medicine Program  CE MED James Scholar Program for Independent Study Rural Medical Education  RMED  Program Curriculum by Year M  Year M  Year M  and M  Years Psychiatry Clerkship Course Management Blackboard Exams Benware Course Evaluations Visiting Students Medical Education and Evaluation MD Student Services and Support Student Affairs Staff Academic Skills Step   Resources Housing Computing Registrar Career Services Scholarship Opportunities Student Financial Planning Student Health and Wellness MD Student Life Rockford Resources Student Organizations Parking   Transportation Diversity Educational Policies Master of Science in Medical Biotechnology Program Master of 